WorldStage NewsOnline— Nigeria’s President Muhammadu Buhari will on Monday address the people  on further steps to take to check the spread of Coronavirus in the country. Mr Aliyu Sani, the national coordinator of the Presidential Task Force (PTF) on COVID-19 confirmed this when he appeared on a TV programme on Sunday. The President on Sunday received briefing from the Chairman of the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19, Mr Boss Mustapha, on the activities of the PTF across the country.